  For this project I will create a small virtual computer network for a therapy clinic. The
clinic must have high security on client information, such as patient records, patient schedules,
check-ins, and secure communication between the workers. Overall, the goal of this project is to
show how different types of networks work together to be able to have a reliable healthcare
system.

  The clinic will have a reception area where the patients will check in, private secure
offices for the therapy session, and an administrative room. Since the staff members will be
dealing with HIPPA there will need to be two different internet systems. The patients who visit
will be able to use an isolated network, while the staff will be using LAN/ NAT to connect to the
internet.

  There will be two different networks, a staff network that is used by the employees and a
client network that is going to be used by the visitors. The network will include a router, a
switch, the staff’s personal computer(s), and a server that has DNS. The router will provide NAT
that will allow the employees to work while the clinic’s information will be secure.

-Device IP address
-Router 192.168.10.1
-Clinic Server 192.168.10.10
-Staff Personal Computer 192.168.10.20
-DNS Server 192.168.10.10

  Overall, throughout this project I will demonstrate how a therapy clinic will need to use a
secure network to be able to operate without worrying about client information being taken.
